# moonproto.conf.example
#
# Example configuration for a moonproto client.
#
# Usage:
#   1. Copy this file to `moonproto.conf` (or any name you prefer).
#   2. Edit the values.
#   3. Read the file in your own code and pass the values into the library.
#      See examples/trading_flow.rs for a minimal connection.
#
# Format: `key = value`, one parameter per line.
# Comments: lines starting with `#` are ignored.
# Blank lines are ignored.
#
# ============================================================================
# NTP - time synchronization
# ============================================================================
#
# NTP server host used to correct the client's local time.
# Used for correct display of application-command timestamps (orders, trades)
# in the UI. NOT used for replay protection or encryption.
#
# Default (if omitted): pool.ntp.org
#
# Alternatives:
#   - time.cloudflare.com
#   - time.google.com
#   - <moonbot-server-ip>:<port> - if the bot provides its own NTP (depends on the server config)
#
ntp_host = pool.ntp.org
